Distance comparisons


Inter- and intra- class distances

Inter-class distances are calculated using the Hamming distance between the different classes. Intra-class distances are calculated using the Hamming distance between the predicted binary masks of the same class.

Below are the summarised results of the inter- and intra-class distances for the COSFIRE and DenseNet models.

  • Test data
  • Test data vs Train data
  • Train data

test_df_cosfire = pd.read_csv("IMR_DNT161_model_data_complete_Sat_Sep_21_15_12_23_2024/test_df.csv")
labels_cosfire_test = test_df_cosfire['label_name'].tolist()

predictions_test = np.loadtxt(
    os.path.join("IMR_DNT161_model_data_complete_Sat_Sep_21_15_12_23_2024", "predictions_test.out"),
    delimiter=','
)
predictions_train = np.loadtxt(
    os.path.join("IMR_DNT161_model_data_complete_Sat_Sep_21_15_12_23_2024", "predictions_train.out"),
    delimiter=','
)

counter = {}
output_list_cosfire_test = [f"{item}_{counter[item]}" if item in counter else f"{item}_1" for item in labels_cosfire_test for counter[item] in (counter.setdefault(item, 0)+1,)]

# Load the Hamming distance matrix
hamming_matrix_cosfire = np.loadtxt(
    "IMR_DNT161_model_data_complete_Sat_Sep_21_15_12_23_2024/hamming_matrix_test.out",
    delimiter=','
)
df_cosfire_test = pd.DataFrame(hamming_matrix_cosfire, columns=output_list_cosfire_test, index=output_list_cosfire_test)

# Plot and save the Hamming distance matrix
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))
plt.imshow(df_cosfire_test, cmap='viridis')
plt.colorbar(label='Hamming distance')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig(os.path.join(output_dir, 'hamming_matrix_test_cosfire.png'))
plt.show()

intra_class_cosfire_test = []
#print('Plotting individual classes:')
for class_label in classes:
    mean_value = process_class(df_cosfire_test, class_label)
    intra_class_cosfire_test.append(mean_value)

# Compute inter-class mean distances for each class
inter_class_cosfire_test = []
for class_label in classes:
    mean_value = compute_inter_class_mean(df_cosfire_test, class_label)
    inter_class_cosfire_test.append(mean_value)

for class_label in classes:
    mean_values = compute_inter_class_mean_class_by_class(df_cosfire_test, class_label)
    inter_class_by_class_cosfire_test_v2.append(mean_values)

df_interclass_test_cosfire_v2 = pd.DataFrame(inter_class_by_class_cosfire_test_v2, index=classes)

df_interclass_test_cosfire_v2.to_csv(output_dir + '/inter_class_by_class_cosfire_test_v2.csv',index=False)

    intra_class_densenet.append(mean_value)

    inter_class_densenet.append(mean_value)
